German Chancellor Angela Merkel issued a warning about rising anti-Semitism on Saturday during remarks for International Holocaust Remembrance Day. "Anti-Semitism, racism and the hatred of others," are on the rise as they haven't been in years, Merkel said. "It is inconceivable and shameful that no Jewish institution can exist without police protection, whether it is a school, a kindergarten or a synagogue." Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
